\begin_layout Itemize
Shares, funds, bonds, ETF - if it's traded on regulated market (stock exchange/m
arket) and you'll keep them 1 year or more, then you are paying no taxes
 and no health insurance (/zdravotne odvody).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If they are not traded on regulated market or you have them for less than
 1 year, then you're paying taxes 19% or 25% (depending on how much money
 it is ...
 it if is less than 176.8x of life minimum, then 19%, of it's higher, then
 25%) and also health insurance (/zdravotne odvody).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
BTW it's FIFO - if you sell a share, and you have 2 shares of the same stock
 (one bought more than 1 year ago and one bought recently), then you are
 not paying taxes on that share, because it's like the oldest one was sold
 - always from oldest (that's why FIFO).
\end_layout

